BRITS The son of former SABC board member Hope Zinde will go on trial in the High Court in Pretoria in June for her murder.Mark Zinde, 23, appeared briefly in the Brits Regional Court on Tuesday and his trial date was set for 12 June.He is accused of killing his 50-year-old mother, a journalist and television news anchor.The state alleges that he killed her at their home in Pecanwood Estate, Hartbeespoort Dam in June last year. He is charged with murder and possession of drugs.His mother s body was found in the boot of her car on 11 June 2016.READ: Hope Zinde s son Mark to undergo psychiatric evaluationZinde was referred for psychiatric evaluation at the Weskoppies Psychiatric Hospital in Pretoria following his arrest in June. The assessment report declared that he was fit to stand trial and capable of understanding court proceedings. The report further stated that he had not been suffering any mental disorder when he allegedly killed his mother.The family insisted that he was not in his right mind at the time. The defence disputed the report and wanted him to be re-admitted t- Weskoppies for a CAT scan and EEG.The court dismissed his application to be admitted again to Weskoppies.In a separate case, Zinde faces a charge of assault with the intention to cause grievous bodily harm, after allegedly attacking his father, Dr Lebohang Manoto, at his Walkerville home, south of Johannesburg t the Vereeniging Magistrate s Court last year.African News Agency